com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2020-01-16T15:14:07Z", "updated_at": "2020-02-06T16:14:36Z", "closed_at": "2020-02-06T16:14:36Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Instead of bloating the command docstrings it would often be helpful to add pointers to handbook content for background info or details.\r\n\r\n\r\nIf I want to do this now, I'd have to add something like this to a docstring\r\n\r\n```\r\n    .. seealso::\r\n\r\n      http://handbook.datalad.org/en/latest/usecases/datastorage_for_institutions.html\r\n        More information on Remote Indexed Archive (RIA) stores\r\n ```\r\n\r\nIt renders nicely in both manpage and HTML docs, but it still ugly, because it will unconditionally reference the latest version of the handbook, and not necessarily the version that corresponds to the running datalad.\r\n\r\n@adswa has started maintaining release branches matching `MAJOR.MINOR` versions of DataLad in the handbook. So we have this URL available now:\r\n\r\nhttp://handbook.datalad.org/en/0.12/usecases/datastorage_for_institutions.html\r\n\r\nNow we could introduce a directive that enables us to place more readable handbook references, that point to the relevant version of the documentation.", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_